latestIgtvVideos.caption:

You can add sophistication to this look by focusing on your cheeks and lips, remembering of course not to overdo it.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Winter Skincare with Facial Oil and Wooden Roller
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
My alluring night-care routine with @ozonesignature Kanaka Taila has helped me in clearing my dark circles and reduce fine lines. It can be used for wrinkles & dull skin. This oil has goodness of Mulethi, Manjistha and Lotus along with Sesame seed oil as the base of the preparation that helps in easy absorption within the skin because of the lower molecular weight. This oil gives me radiant glow on my skin.
Take 5-6 drops of oil and use it below under eye with your finger tip and then generously dab all over the face. This oil is very useful in increasing the blood circulation within the skin.
A night care routine is very essential for repairing, healing & maintenance of healthy skin.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Monsoon Hair Care Hair Fall Rescue Ritual 🌿
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Oily scalp, hair fall and dandruff are the problems that crop up during the monsoon. We all love the rains but this is also a season that demands extra care for our tresses. Following proper monsoon hair care hygiene can be helpful in tackling these issues. 
First and foremost requirement is regular hair wash. Hair should be washed in frequent intervals during monsoon as delay could lead to oily scalp, excessive hair fall, dandruff and roughness. 

Let me take you through my
“Monsoon Hair Care hair fall rescue ritual with Forest Essentials” @forestessentials 
 
Step 1 – Massage your head with Ayurvedic Herb Enriched Head Massage Oil Bhringraj

Step - 2 Wash your scalp with Bhringraj & Shikakai Hair Cleanser

Step 3 – Condition your hair with Bhringraj & Shikakai Hair Conditioner   
 
Step 4 - Rejuvenate Your Hair with Hair Vitalizer Bhringraj
